messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the user-route implementation (paths relative to project root):

- routes/userRoutes.js
- controllers/userController.js

Explanation:
- server.js mounts userRoutes at /api/users. The routing definitions live in routes/userRoutes.js (it wires HTTP paths to handler functions and applies auth middleware).
- The actual request handler implementations (the controllers) are in controllers/userController.js â€” this file implements all handlers exported and referenced by routes/userRoutes.js (authUser, registerUser, logoutUser, getUserProfile, updateUserProfile, getUsers, deleteUser, getUserById, updateUser).
- Note: routes/userRoutes.js imports protect/admin middleware from middleware/authMiddleware.js to guard certain routes, but the handlers themselves are implemented in controllers/userController.js.
